A portion of the building of the office of Gauteng premier David Makhura caught fire this morning. Makhura spokesperson Phumla Sekonyane said all officials have been evacuated&nbsp;and they are safe.The Johannesburg emergency services are on site to extinguish the fire.&nbsp;Sekonyane said they don't have information as to what could have caused the fire.Makhura was not at the office.